        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4485360791" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6612168371761656542">An early work by renowned historian Barbara W. Tuchman, <i>The Zimmermann Telegram</i> recounts the events leading up to the US joining WWI. Informative and covers a lot of ground, though I rather hoped to see more focus on the interception and decoding of the eponymous telegram and less on... well... everything else going on around the world at the time. I also can&apos;t say I cared much for the at times rather condescending tone, which was amplified by a somewhat unfortunate combination of author and nar</span>
  <span id="freeText6612168371761656542" style="display:none">An early work by renowned historian Barbara W. Tuchman, <i>The Zimmermann Telegram</i> recounts the events leading up to the US joining WWI. Informative and covers a lot of ground, though I rather hoped to see more focus on the interception and decoding of the eponymous telegram and less on... well... everything else going on around the world at the time. I also can't say I cared much for the at times rather condescending tone, which was amplified by a somewhat unfortunate combination of author and narrator.</span>
  <a data-text-id="6612168371761656542" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

