    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3775503003?book_show_action=true">Jan 18, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Iain" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Iain" href="/user/show/10869554-iain">Iain</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/10869554-iain?shelf=folio-society">folio-society</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3775503003" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16698801128437595549">Folio Society Edition. Fascinating insight into how America, and reluctant President Woodrow Wilson, was finally drawn into the First World War on the side of the Allies, including intrigue in Mexico and all hinging on a single telegraph message intercepted and decoded by the British. Historical writing as dramatic political thriller.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


